The paper proposes a new approach to visualize saliency maps for deep neural network models and applies it to deep reinforcement learning agents trained on Atari environments. This involves adding an attention module to the feature extractor of an established baseline, resulting in a trainable model that can produce saliency maps. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new approach to visualize saliency maps for deep neural network models, which is a subfield of machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper applies the proposed approach to deep reinforcement learning agents, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper involves visualizing saliency maps, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper involves deep neural network models, which is a subfield of neural computing. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper evaluates saliency metrics on the Atari-HEAD dataset of human gameplay, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction.
